# Daily Todo Handoff

Use this rule when the user asks to start from a todo file, daily task list, sprint note, or today's todo.

## Before Starting Today's Todo

If the todo source includes prior-day context, yesterday's work, completed items, blockers, or a dated history, ask once before starting:

> Before I start today's todo, do you want a quick recap of what was done yesterday?

If the user says yes, summarize:

- What was completed yesterday.
- What remains open.
- Known blockers, risks, or handoffs.
- The first suggested item for today.

If the user says no, start today's todo directly.

## When Not To Ask

- Do not ask if there is no visible prior-day context.
- Do not ask repeatedly in the same work session.
- Do not block urgent user instructions; if the user gives a direct task, proceed and mention any relevant yesterday context only if it changes the work.

## Handoff Quality

Keep the recap short and factual. Separate completed work from assumptions, and call out stale TODOs that may no longer match the current code.
